      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for merging :)\n\nAnd for the next step, I am thinking about starting the `git grep` part of\nthe issue as a small backend-first change.\n\nMy initial scope would be JSON only, without any UI:\n\n```\n  /repo/+grep/\u003crevision\u003e?q\u003d\u003ctext\u003e\u0026format\u003dJSON\n  /repo/+grep/\u003crevision\u003e/\u003cpath-prefix\u003e?q\u003d\u003ctext\u003e\u0026format\u003dJSON\n```\n\nThe implementation would use JGit `TreeWalk`/`ObjectReader` directly, with\nlimits on number of results and blob size, and would not add any indexing dependency.\n\nDoes this endpoint shape and scope sound reasonable as the next step?",
      "revId": "7a34d138a61916f3c0e1ed540b2a4f7c8eb35375",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
